    • Constructor Detail

      • Categorical

        public Categorical(java.lang.String name,
                   int cardinality,
                   java.util.ArrayList<Expression> knownConstants)
        Creates a categorical type of given name, cardinality and known constants; unknown constants, if requested, are named "1", ... "n", where name is the lower-case version of given name, and n is cardinality minus number of known constants.
        Parameters:
        name -
        cardinality - number of elements in type (-1 if unknown, -2 if infinite)
        knownConstants -

      • Categorical

        public Categorical(java.lang.String name,
                   int cardinality,
                   java.lang.String knownConstantPrefix,
                   int numberOfKnownConstants)
        Similar to Categorical(String, int, ArrayList), but known constants are specified how many there are as well as a prefix for their name; for example, if the prefix is "a" and the number of known constants is specified as 100, then the known constants of this categorical type will be a1,...,a100. Currently, this simply creates all known constants explicitly in an array list; in the future, that may be replaced by some sort of virtual Collection implementation.
        Parameters:
        name -
        cardinality -
        knownConstantPrefix -
        numberOfKnownConstants -
